            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36.7b"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">76</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint"> 
                    <figure/>
                        
                    <hi rend="caps">ACHARYA
                        <lb/>
                    INDIRA GANDHI
                        <lb/>
                        
                    UPACHARYA
                        <lb/>
                    KALIDAS BHATTACHARYA
                        <lb/>
                        
                    VIÅšVA-BHARATI
                        <lb/>   
                    FOUNDED BY RABINDRANATH TAGORE 
                        <lb/>
                        
                    SANTINIKETAN
                        <lb/>
                    WEST BENGAL, INDIA
                        <lb/>
                    TELEPHONE: BOLPUR JN.</hi> 2,3, &amp; 4
                </fw>
                
                <note>ans 12/11/72</note>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>1-12-1972</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Your kind letter of November 10 took some time before reaching. But the book <hi rend="caps">ALL IS BUT A BEGINNING</hi> followed soon after. I have read it at one breath (ours is the land of breath control, so I had no difficulty). How I laughed and laughed! I could imagine myself sitting by your side. I look forwward to the sequence. I am sure it will receive rave reviews.</p> 
                
                <p>Oh, I wish I had met Miss Kelly on the Acropolis. We could have done a Chorus -- from your bardic poems. Better luck next time.</p>
                
                <p>Re books: I sent a copy of <hi rend="caps">MINE OYSTER</hi>, a collection of essays in which you figure prominently, some months back by sea mail. If it has not reched so far, it should shortly. Another, a smaller work: <hi rend="caps">SRI AUROBINDO: POET</hi> was sent the other day by air mail. This may have reached by now. I shall be happy t<del>t</del><add>o</add> have your reactions, if and when you are free.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>With all good wishes, always,</salute> 
                    <salute>Yours as ever,</salute> 
                    
                    <signed>Eveir</signed> 
                    
                    <note type="authorial">(this is better)</note>
                
                    <hi rend="underline">Dr John Neihardt</hi> 
                </closer>
                
                <fw>2</fw>
                
            </div1>
